Invitation paragraph
You are invited to participate in the above named study. Please read the document
carefully and ask your doctor questions or seek clarification if anything is not clear to
you. This form provides you information about the study and explains the benefits and
risks if any of participation in the study. You may discuss with your family, friends, and
family doctor if needed. When all your questions and misgivings have been answered to
your satisfaction and if you are willing to participate in the study, you will be required to
sign the consent form. You will be provided with a copy of the information sheet for your
reference.

How many subjects will be participating in the study?

Is my participation compulsory?
No, your participation is voluntary and non-participation will not in any way affect
your treatment at the hospital.
Can I withdraw from the study?
You are free to withdraw from the study at any time without giving any explanation. This will
not affect your care at the hospital. No further test(s) will be done or data collected.
However, the data already collected may be used, unless you do not permit.
*Along with English version of the PIS, translations in regional language have to be submitted.
Translation in regional language need not be literal. It should convey the information in a simple
language .If necessary take help of professional translators.

What about the confidentiality of my data?
All the information obtained in this study will be kept strictly confidential and used for
scientific purposes only. Data taken from this study may be published or presented in
scientific meetings. However your name and other identifying information will be kept
confidential and will not be made publicly available. Investigators, ethics committee
members & regulatory authorities may review your personal and medical records if required.
Is the study approved by the institutional ethics committee?
Yes. The study has been reviewed & approved by the Hinduja Hospital Institutional Review
Board
